<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1330">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/103.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Davis</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Guadalajara</hi>
                                </placeName> (<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-11-05T23:59:59-05:00" notBefore="1914-10-22T00:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; received November 5,
                                    1914</hi>).</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to confirm my telegram
                            to you on October 17. I afterwards came in possession of facts in
                            connection with the concession of the Compañía Galletera Nacional which
                            in substance are these: In the articles of concession the Company was
                            exempt from all kind of taxation for a term of twenty years (State
                            taxation), but <pb facs="0897" n="781" xml:id="pg_781"/> the
                            concessionaires waived all rights as foreigners in any and everything
                            pertaining to its affairs.</p>
                        <p>This latter clause is upon what hinges the persistence of the local
                            authorities here in prosecuting the matter, is my opinion.</p>
                        <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Will B. Davis</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>